Docs.summary: Specifies the duration value in a multilanguage lookup table of the Duration type.

remarks.para: The duration value is in tenths of a minute. For example, if the working day is eight hours, the duration value for one working day is 4800 (8 hours x 60 minutes/hour x 10 tenths/minute). If the LT_VALUE_DUR is specified, the must also be specified.
If the lookup table is not a Duration type, then the LT_VALUE_DUR property is a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).

Docs.summary: Shows the full value of a multilevel lookup table node, including the parent values with separator characters.

remarks.para: For example, if the parent node value of a multilanguage lookup table of type Text is England, the child value is Sussex, and the separator character is a caret ("^"), the full value of the child node is England^Sussex.
